3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper involves the study of algebraic structures and their properties, which can be seen as a type of data structure. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Although less likely, the study of codes and their properties can also be applied to network coding and communication in social and information networks.
